<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-2067] refactor o.a.c.utils.UUIDGen to allow creating type 1 UUIDs for a given time</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-2067</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-2027&quot; title=&quot;term definitions&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-2027&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-2027&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; creates the need to generate type 1 UUIDs using arbitrary date/times.  IMO, this would be a good opportunity to replace o.a.c.utils.UUIDGen with the class that Gary Dusbabek wrote for Flewton (&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/flewton/flewton/blob/master/src/com/rackspace/flewton/util/UUIDGen.java&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/flewton/flewton/blob/master/src/com/rackspace/flewton/util/UUIDGen.java&lt;/a&gt;), which is better/more comprehensive.  We can even eliminate the dependency on JUG.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Patches to follow.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
